5D23008C.Line1.B79B1: I once schooled the boy Yorin in the old ways. His mother Braega too, as she wrote her chronicles. Both of them had a deep respect for our culture.

F7177A0E.Line3.B79B1: Braega inspired me to catalogue some of our more ancient artifacts. In doing so, she reminded me of how easily the past can be forgotten.
